<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f110292021721889>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Knight's Blessing proc</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Dec 13th 1:40 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=209144><span id= >LikeUntoGod</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>On one hand it should be a better Weapon but pretty good for a LDoN drop, I got this as a drop and I was useing a Mace of Dark Glory with the same Proc and a Brightstar Buckler. I sorta wish that I had not spent&nbsp;&nbsp;so much on a attunable (no-drop) Shield. I often 3 to 4 box with 6 accounts on 4 computers. So I find that to get full use of the shield I must hit Bash etc. So in a way I would rather have a awesome 2 hdr. Plus, like the old D&amp;D &quot;to hit&quot; rules, I think a weapon with higher Dmg hits mobs with Higher AC better. It seems so to me. <br><br>The Mace of Dark Glory also has great stats and I added a 50 HP Vampire proc to it from the BB LDoN. That procs more then the Knight's Blessing but together they can at times heal him completely. I wish Pallies etc could put a proc on their Shields. They get a little screwed on that.<br><br>I'm not a great upper level player etc but I know of another 2ndr staff a higher level Guildmate has with much greater stats and the same Knight's Blessing on it. It is called the Resplendent War Maul and beyound what I can ever get. <br><br>I have been playing since the beginning of EQ and this would have been considered a awesome weapon but with so many &quot;super&quot; weapons today it does not stand out. However, I like the concept of being able to heal myself and I almost have enough LDoN points for the 75 HP Vampire Kiss which I will put on the hammer of Silent Screams. I have really stressed Dex in Augs and AA's so I proc flairly well. <br><br>Still, I am a Dmg taker rather then a Dmg dealer. But if you do like I do sometime and cut some chars items to the bone ( moneywise ) , this Free to 1,500pp  weapon is a good deal. <br><br>Btway, I also 